      "writtenOn": "2021-01-05T18:45:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think that this part could be rephrased slightly for clarity.\n\nFrom the first part, I see that `now` will be written to CreateTime or UpdateTime of entities that are created or modified, and from looking up datastore.RoundTime I see that datastore saves only the microsecond level... Does the second part here mean that run.Run is one of those entities that is created or modified? (Potentially you don\u0027t need to mention this, if we want to store rounded time values datastore in general?)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 263,
