      "writtenOn": "2021-01-05T18:58:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Facts:\n Datastore stores time up to us precision.\n Go\u0027s time.Time has ns precision.\n\nThus, writing arbitrary time.Time into Datastore followed by reading it back results in precision loss.\nRoundTime emulates this loss.\n\nSo, I use it immediately, s.t. returned object is exactly the same as if it was read from datastore after the transaction.\n\n1. Does it make sense?\n2. Any better way to phrase my comment in code?",
